  <p class="field-row"><span class="field-label">US Army branch:</span> Infantry (later General Staff Corps)</p>
  <p class="field-row"><span class="field-label">US citizenship:</span> Naturalized 12 July 1945, Augsburg, Germany (certificate AM 20958) &mdash; AFTER VE Day</p>
  <p class="field-row"><span class="field-label">US Army ranks:</span> Captain (commissioned 16 May 1943) &rarr; Major (September 1944) &rarr; Lieutenant Colonel (September 1945)</p>
  <p class="field-row"><span class="field-label">US Army service dates:</span> 16 May 1943 &ndash; 9 March 1946 (separated Fort Dix, NJ); recalled to active duty May 1951</p>
  <p class="field-row"><span class="field-label">Primary WWII role:</span> Chief, Foreign Liaison Branch, G-2 Section, HQ 12th Army Group (from 1 August 1944)</p>
  <p class="field-row"><span class="field-label">Key action:</span> Prepared the cease-fire order signed by the German commander of Paris, 25 August 1944</p>
  <p class="field-row"><span class="field-label">Polish Army service:</span> Sub-lieutenant of Cavalry Reserve; September 1939 campaign; Government-in-Exile 1939&ndash;1941</p>
